  508:  2: name: gitnexus-cli
  509:  3: description: "Use when the user needs to run GitNexus CLI commands like analyze/index a repo, check status, clean the index, generate a wiki, or list indexed repos. Examples: \"Index this repo\", \"Reanalyze the codebase\", \"Generate a wiki\""
  510:  4: ---
  511:  5: 
  512:  6: # GitNexus CLI Commands
  513:  7: 
  514:  8: Commands below use `node .gitnexus/run.cjs <command>` — the project-local runner `gitnexus analyze` drops next to the index. It auto-selects an available runner at call time (global `gitnexus`, else `pnpm dlx`, else `npx`), so no package-manager assumption and no global install is required.
  515:  9: 
  516: 10: > **Not analyzed yet, or `node .gitnexus/run.cjs` reports `Cannot find module`** (the gitignored runner is absent — e.g. a fresh clone or `git clean`)? (Re)generate it with `npx gitnexus analyze` from the project root. On **npm 11.x**, if `npx` crashes during install (`node.target is null`), install once with `npm i -g gitnexus` (then `gitnexus analyze`) or use `pnpm --allow-build=@ladybugdb/core --allow-build=gitnexus --allow-build=tree-sitter dlx gitnexus@latest analyze`. See [#1939](https://github.com/abhigyanpatwari/GitNexus/issues/1939).
  517: 11: 
  518: 12: ## Commands
  519: 13: 
  520: 14: ### analyze — Build or refresh the index
  521: 15: 
  522: 16: ```bash
  523: 17: node .gitnexus/run.cjs analyze
  524: 18: ```
  525: 19: 
  526: 20: Run from the project root. This parses all source files, builds the knowledge graph, writes it to `.gitnexus/`, and generates CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md context files.
  527: 21: 
  528: 22: | Flag           | Effect                                                           |
  529: 23: | -------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------- |
  530: 24: | `--force`      | Force full re-index even if up to date                           |
  531: 25: | `--embeddings` | Enable embedding generation for semantic search (off by default) |
  532: 26: | `--drop-embeddings` | Drop existing embeddings on rebuild. By default, an `analyze` without `--embeddings` preserves them. |
  533: 27: 
  534: 28: **When to run:** First time in a project, after major code changes, or when `gitnexus://repo/{name}/context` reports the index is stale. In Claude Code, a PostToolUse hook detects staleness after `git commit` and `git merge` and notifies the agent to run `analyze` — the hook does not run analyze itself, to avoid blocking the agent for up to 120s and risking KuzuDB corruption on timeout.
  535: 29: 
  536: 30: ### status — Check index freshness
  537: 31: 
  538: 32: ```bash
  539: 33: node .gitnexus/run.cjs status
  540: 34: ```
  541: 35: 
  542: 36: Shows whether the current repo has a GitNexus index, when it was last updated, and symbol/relationship counts. Use this to check if re-indexing is needed.
  543: 37: 
  544: 38: ### clean — Delete the index
  545: 39: 
  546: 40: ```bash
  547: 41: node .gitnexus/run.cjs clean
  548: 42: ```
  549: 43: 
  550: 44: Deletes the `.gitnexus/` directory and unregisters the repo from the global registry. Use before re-indexing if the index is corrupt or after removing GitNexus from a project.
  551: 45: 
  552: 46: | Flag      | Effect                                            |
  553: 47: | --------- | ------------------------------------------------- |
  554: 48: | `--force` | Skip confirmation prompt                          |
  555: 49: | `--all`   | Clean all indexed repos, not just the current one |
  556: 50: 
  557: 51: ### wiki — Generate documentation from the graph
  558: 52: 
  559: 53: ```bash
  560: 54: node .gitnexus/run.cjs wiki
  561: 55: ```
  562: 56: 
  563: 57: Generates repository documentation from the knowledge graph using an LLM. Requires an API key (saved to `~/.gitnexus/config.json` on first use).
  564: 58: 
  565: 59: | Flag                | Effect                                    |
  566: 60: | ------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
  567: 61: | `--force`           | Force full regeneration                   |
  568: 62: | `--model <model>`   | LLM model (default: minimax/minimax-m2.5) |
  569: 63: | `--base-url <url>`  | LLM API base URL                          |
  570: 64: | `--api-key <key>`   | LLM API key                               |
  571: 65: | `--concurrency <n>` | Parallel LLM calls (default: 3)           |
  572: 66: | `--gist`            | Publish wiki as a public GitHub Gist      |
  573: 67: 
  574: 68: ### list — Show all indexed repos
  575: 69: 
  576: 70: ```bash
  577: 71: node .gitnexus/run.cjs list
  578: 72: ```
  579: 73: 
  580: 74: Lists all repositories registered in `~/.gitnexus/registry.json`. The MCP `list_repos` tool provides the same information.
  581: 75: 
  582: 76: ## After Indexing
  583: 77: 
  584: 78: 1. **Read `gitnexus://repo/{name}/context`** to verify the index loaded
  585: 79: 2. Use the other GitNexus skills (`exploring`, `debugging`, `impact-analysis`, `refactoring`) for your task
  586: 80: 
  587: 81: ## Troubleshooting
  588: 82: 
  589: 83: - **"Not inside a git repository"**: Run from a directory inside a git repo
  590: 84: - **Index is stale after re-analyzing**: Restart Claude Code to reload the MCP server
  591: 85: - **Embeddings slow**: Omit `--embeddings` (it's off by default) or set `OPENAI_API_KEY` for faster API-based embedding
  592: </file>
