  594:   1: ---
  595:   2: name: gitnexus-debugging
  596:   3: description: "Use when the user is debugging a bug, tracing an error, or asking why something fails. Examples: \"Why is X failing?\", \"Where does this error come from?\", \"Trace this bug\""
  597:   4: ---
  598:   5: 
  599:   6: # Debugging with GitNexus
  600:   7: 
  601:   8: ## When to Use
  602:   9: 
  603:  10: - "Why is this function failing?"
  604:  11: - "Trace where this error comes from"
  605:  12: - "Who calls this method?"
  606:  13: - "This endpoint returns 500"
  607:  14: - Investigating bugs, errors, or unexpected behavior
  608:  15: 
  609:  16: ## Workflow
  610:  17: 
  611:  18: ```
  612:  19: 1. query({search_query: "<error or symptom>"})            → Find related execution flows
  613:  20: 2. context({name: "<suspect>"})                    → See callers/callees/processes
  614:  21: 3. READ gitnexus://repo/{name}/process/{name}                → Trace execution flow
  615:  22: 4. cypher({statement: "MATCH path..."})                 → Custom traces if needed
  616:  23: ```
  617:  24: 
  618:  25: > If "Index is stale" → run `node .gitnexus/run.cjs analyze` in terminal.
  619:  26: 
  620:  27: ## Checklist
  621:  28: 
  622:  29: ```
  623:  30: - [ ] Understand the symptom (error message, unexpected behavior)
  624:  31: - [ ] query for error text or related code
  625:  32: - [ ] Identify the suspect function from returned processes
  626:  33: - [ ] context to see callers and callees
  627:  34: - [ ] Trace execution flow via process resource if applicable
  628:  35: - [ ] cypher for custom call chain traces if needed
  629:  36: - [ ] Read source files to confirm root cause
  630:  37: ```
  631:  38: 
  632:  39: ## Debugging Patterns
  633:  40: 
  634:  41: | Symptom              | GitNexus Approach                                          |
  635:  42: | -------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- |
  636:  43: | Error message        | `query` for error text → `context` on throw sites |
  637:  44: | Wrong return value   | `context` on the function → trace callees for data flow    |
  638:  45: | Intermittent failure | `context` → look for external calls, async deps            |
  639:  46: | Performance issue    | `context` → find symbols with many callers (hot paths)     |
  640:  47: | Recent regression    | `detect_changes` to see what your changes affect           |
  641:  48: | "How does A reach B?" | `trace` between the two symbols — shortest call chain in one call |
  642:  49: 
  643:  50: ## Tools
  644:  51: 
  645:  52: **query** — find code related to error:
  646:  53: 
  647:  54: ```
  648:  55: query({search_query: "payment validation error"})
  649:  56: → Processes: CheckoutFlow, ErrorHandling
  650:  57: → Symbols: validatePayment, handlePaymentError, PaymentException
  651:  58: ```
  652:  59: 
  653:  60: **context** — full context for a suspect:
  654:  61: 
  655:  62: ```
  656:  63: context({name: "validatePayment"})
  657:  64: → Incoming calls: processCheckout, webhookHandler
  658:  65: → Outgoing calls: verifyCard, fetchRates (external API!)
  659:  66: → Processes: CheckoutFlow (step 3/7)
  660:  67: ```
  661:  68: 
  662:  69: **cypher** — custom call chain traces:
  663:  70: 
  664:  71: ```cypher
  665:  72: MATCH path = (a)-[:CodeRelation {type: 'CALLS'}*1..2]->(b:Function {name: "validatePayment"})
  666:  73: RETURN [n IN nodes(path) | n.name] AS chain
  667:  74: ```
  668:  75: 
  669:  76: **trace** — shortest call chain between two symbols ("how does A reach B?"), one call instead of chaining `context` hops:
  670:  77: 
  671:  78: ```
  672:  79: trace({ from: "processCheckout", to: "fetchRates" })
  673:  80: → status: ok, hopCount: 3
  674:  81: → hops: processCheckout → validatePayment → verifyCard → fetchRates
  675:  82: → edges: CALLS (1.0), CALLS (0.95), CALLS (1.0)
  676:  83: ```
  677:  84: 
  678:  85: When no path exists, `trace` reports the furthest reachable node — exactly where the chain breaks (dynamic dispatch, reflection, or an external boundary).
  679:  86: 
  680:  87: ## Example: "Payment endpoint returns 500 intermittently"
  681:  88: 
  682:  89: ```
  683:  90: 1. query({search_query: "payment error handling"})
  684:  91:    → Processes: CheckoutFlow, ErrorHandling
  685:  92:    → Symbols: validatePayment, handlePaymentError
  686:  93: 
  687:  94: 2. context({name: "validatePayment"})
  688:  95:    → Outgoing calls: verifyCard, fetchRates (external API!)
  689:  96: 
  690:  97: 3. READ gitnexus://repo/my-app/process/CheckoutFlow
  691:  98:    → Step 3: validatePayment → calls fetchRates (external)
  692:  99: 
  693: 100: 4. Root cause: fetchRates calls external API without proper timeout
  694: 101: ```
  695: </file>
