  700:  4: ---
  701:  5: 
  702:  6: # Exploring Codebases with GitNexus
  703:  7: 
  704:  8: ## When to Use
  705:  9: 
  706: 10: - "How does authentication work?"
  707: 11: - "What's the project structure?"
  708: 12: - "Show me the main components"
  709: 13: - "Where is the database logic?"
  710: 14: - Understanding code you haven't seen before
  711: 15: 
  712: 16: ## Workflow
  713: 17: 
  714: 18: ```
  715: 19: 1. READ gitnexus://repos                          → Discover indexed repos
  716: 20: 2. READ gitnexus://repo/{name}/context             → Codebase overview, check staleness
  717: 21: 3. query({search_query: "<what you want to understand>"})  → Find related execution flows
  718: 22: 4. context({name: "<symbol>"})            → Deep dive on specific symbol
  719: 23: 5. READ gitnexus://repo/{name}/process/{name}      → Trace full execution flow
  720: 24: ```
  721: 25: 
  722: 26: > If step 2 says "Index is stale" → run `node .gitnexus/run.cjs analyze` in terminal.
  723: 27: 
  724: 28: ## Checklist
  725: 29: 
  726: 30: ```
  727: 31: - [ ] READ gitnexus://repo/{name}/context
  728: 32: - [ ] query for the concept you want to understand
  729: 33: - [ ] Review returned processes (execution flows)
  730: 34: - [ ] context on key symbols for callers/callees
  731: 35: - [ ] READ process resource for full execution traces
  732: 36: - [ ] Read source files for implementation details
  733: 37: ```
  734: 38: 
  735: 39: ## Resources
  736: 40: 
  737: 41: | Resource                                | What you get                                            |
  738: 42: | --------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
  739: 43: | `gitnexus://repo/{name}/context`        | Stats, staleness warning (~150 tokens)                  |
  740: 44: | `gitnexus://repo/{name}/clusters`       | All functional areas with cohesion scores (~300 tokens) |
  741: 45: | `gitnexus://repo/{name}/cluster/{name}` | Area members with file paths (~500 tokens)              |
  742: 46: | `gitnexus://repo/{name}/process/{name}` | Step-by-step execution trace (~200 tokens)              |
  743: 47: 
  744: 48: ## Tools
  745: 49: 
  746: 50: **query** — find execution flows related to a concept:
  747: 51: 
  748: 52: ```
  749: 53: query({search_query: "payment processing"})
  750: 54: → Processes: CheckoutFlow, RefundFlow, WebhookHandler
  751: 55: → Symbols grouped by flow with file locations
  752: 56: ```
  753: 57: 
  754: 58: **context** — 360-degree view of a symbol:
  755: 59: 
  756: 60: ```
  757: 61: context({name: "validateUser"})
  758: 62: → Incoming calls: loginHandler, apiMiddleware
  759: 63: → Outgoing calls: checkToken, getUserById
  760: 64: → Processes: LoginFlow (step 2/5), TokenRefresh (step 1/3)
  761: 65: ```
  762: 66: 
  763: 67: ## Example: "How does payment processing work?"
  764: 68: 
  765: 69: ```
  766: 70: 1. READ gitnexus://repo/my-app/context       → 918 symbols, 45 processes
  767: 71: 2. query({search_query: "payment processing"})
  768: 72:    → CheckoutFlow: processPayment → validateCard → chargeStripe
  769: 73:    → RefundFlow: initiateRefund → calculateRefund → processRefund
  770: 74: 3. context({name: "processPayment"})
  771: 75:    → Incoming: checkoutHandler, webhookHandler
  772: 76:    → Outgoing: validateCard, chargeStripe, saveTransaction
  773: 77: 4. Read src/payments/processor.ts for implementation details
  774: 78: ```
  775: </file>
