  907:  1: ---
  908:  2: name: gitnexus-impact-analysis
  909:  3: description: "Use when the user wants to know what will break if they change something, or needs safety analysis before editing code. Examples: \"Is it safe to change X?\", \"What depends on this?\", \"What will break?\""
  910:  4: ---
  911:  5: 
  912:  6: # Impact Analysis with GitNexus
  913:  7: 
  914:  8: ## When to Use
  915:  9: 
  916: 10: - "Is it safe to change this function?"
  917: 11: - "What will break if I modify X?"
  918: 12: - "Show me the blast radius"
  919: 13: - "Who uses this code?"
  920: 14: - Before making non-trivial code changes
  921: 15: - Before committing — to understand what your changes affect
  922: 16: 
  923: 17: ## Workflow
  924: 18: 
  925: 19: ```
  926: 20: 1. impact({target: "X", direction: "upstream"})  → What depends on this
  927: 21: 2. READ gitnexus://repo/{name}/processes                   → Check affected execution flows
  928: 22: 3. detect_changes()                               → Map current git changes to affected flows
  929: 23: 4. Assess risk and report to user
  930: 24: ```
  931: 25: 
  932: 26: > If "Index is stale" → run `node .gitnexus/run.cjs analyze` in terminal.
  933: 27: 
  934: 28: ## Checklist
  935: 29: 
  936: 30: ```
  937: 31: - [ ] impact({target, direction: "upstream"}) to find dependents
  938: 32: - [ ] Review d=1 items first (these WILL BREAK)
  939: 33: - [ ] Check high-confidence (>0.8) dependencies
  940: 34: - [ ] READ processes to check affected execution flows
  941: 35: - [ ] detect_changes() for pre-commit check
  942: 36: - [ ] Assess risk level and report to user
  943: 37: ```
  944: 38: 
  945: 39: ## Understanding Output
  946: 40: 
  947: 41: | Depth | Risk Level       | Meaning                  |
  948: 42: | ----- | ---------------- | ------------------------ |
  949: 43: | d=1   | **WILL BREAK**   | Direct callers/importers |
  950: 44: | d=2   | LIKELY AFFECTED  | Indirect dependencies    |
  951: 45: | d=3   | MAY NEED TESTING | Transitive effects       |
  952: 46: 
  953: 47: ## Risk Assessment
  954: 48: 
  955: 49: | Affected                       | Risk     |
  956: 50: | ------------------------------ | -------- |
  957: 51: | <5 symbols, few processes      | LOW      |
  958: 52: | 5-15 symbols, 2-5 processes    | MEDIUM   |
  959: 53: | >15 symbols or many processes  | HIGH     |
  960: 54: | Critical path (auth, payments) | CRITICAL |
  961: 55: 
  962: 56: ## Tools
  963: 57: 
  964: 58: **impact** — the primary tool for symbol blast radius:
  965: 59: 
  966: 60: ```
  967: 61: impact({
  968: 62:   target: "validateUser",
  969: 63:   direction: "upstream",
  970: 64:   minConfidence: 0.8,
  971: 65:   maxDepth: 3
  972: 66: })
  973: 67: 
  974: 68: → d=1 (WILL BREAK):
  975: 69:   - loginHandler (src/auth/login.ts:42) [CALLS, 100%]
  976: 70:   - apiMiddleware (src/api/middleware.ts:15) [CALLS, 100%]
  977: 71: 
  978: 72: → d=2 (LIKELY AFFECTED):
  979: 73:   - authRouter (src/routes/auth.ts:22) [CALLS, 95%]
  980: 74: ```
  981: 75: 
  982: 76: **detect_changes** — git-diff based impact analysis:
  983: 77: 
  984: 78: ```
  985: 79: detect_changes({scope: "staged"})
  986: 80: 
  987: 81: → Changed: 5 symbols in 3 files
  988: 82: → Affected: LoginFlow, TokenRefresh, APIMiddlewarePipeline
  989: 83: → Risk: MEDIUM
  990: 84: ```
  991: 85: 
  992: 86: ## Example: "What breaks if I change validateUser?"
  993: 87: 
  994: 88: ```
  995: 89: 1. impact({target: "validateUser", direction: "upstream"})
  996: 90:    → d=1: loginHandler, apiMiddleware (WILL BREAK)
  997: 91:    → d=2: authRouter, sessionManager (LIKELY AFFECTED)
  998: 92: 
  999: 93: 2. READ gitnexus://repo/my-app/processes
 1000: 94:    → LoginFlow and TokenRefresh touch validateUser
 1001: 95: 
 1002: 96: 3. Risk: 2 direct callers, 2 processes = MEDIUM
 1003: 97: ```
