 1005: <file path=".claude/skills/gitnexus/gitnexus-refactoring/SKILL.md">
 1006:   1: ---
 1007:   2: name: gitnexus-refactoring
 1008:   3: description: "Use when the user wants to rename, extract, split, move, or restructure code safely. Examples: \"Rename this function\", \"Extract this into a module\", \"Refactor this class\", \"Move this to a separate file\""
 1009:   4: ---
 1010:   5: 
 1011:   6: # Refactoring with GitNexus
 1012:   7: 
 1013:   8: ## When to Use
 1014:   9: 
 1015:  10: - "Rename this function safely"
 1016:  11: - "Extract this into a module"
 1017:  12: - "Split this service"
 1018:  13: - "Move this to a new file"
 1019:  14: - Any task involving renaming, extracting, splitting, or restructuring code
 1020:  15: 
 1021:  16: ## Workflow
 1022:  17: 
 1023:  18: ```
 1024:  19: 1. impact({target: "X", direction: "upstream"})  → Map all dependents
 1025:  20: 2. query({search_query: "X"})                            → Find execution flows involving X
 1026:  21: 3. context({name: "X"})                           → See all incoming/outgoing refs
 1027:  22: 4. Plan update order: interfaces → implementations → callers → tests
 1028:  23: ```
 1029:  24: 
 1030:  25: > If "Index is stale" → run `node .gitnexus/run.cjs analyze` in terminal.
 1031:  26: 
 1032:  27: ## Checklists
 1033:  28: 
 1034:  29: ### Rename Symbol
 1035:  30: 
 1036:  31: ```
 1037:  32: - [ ] rename({symbol_name: "oldName", new_name: "newName", dry_run: true}) — preview all edits
 1038:  33: - [ ] Review graph edits (high confidence) and ast_search edits (review carefully)
 1039:  34: - [ ] If satisfied: rename({..., dry_run: false}) — apply edits
 1040:  35: - [ ] detect_changes() — verify only expected files changed
 1041:  36: - [ ] Run tests for affected processes
 1042:  37: ```
 1043:  38: 
 1044:  39: ### Extract Module
 1045:  40: 
 1046:  41: ```
 1047:  42: - [ ] context({name: target}) — see all incoming/outgoing refs
 1048:  43: - [ ] impact({target, direction: "upstream"}) — find all external callers
 1049:  44: - [ ] Define new module interface
 1050:  45: - [ ] Extract code, update imports
 1051:  46: - [ ] detect_changes() — verify affected scope
 1052:  47: - [ ] Run tests for affected processes
 1053:  48: ```
 1054:  49: 
 1055:  50: ### Split Function/Service
 1056:  51: 
 1057:  52: ```
 1058:  53: - [ ] context({name: target}) — understand all callees
 1059:  54: - [ ] Group callees by responsibility
 1060:  55: - [ ] impact({target, direction: "upstream"}) — map callers to update
 1061:  56: - [ ] Create new functions/services
 1062:  57: - [ ] Update callers
 1063:  58: - [ ] detect_changes() — verify affected scope
 1064:  59: - [ ] Run tests for affected processes
 1065:  60: ```
 1066:  61: 
 1067:  62: ## Tools
 1068:  63: 
 1069:  64: **rename** — automated multi-file rename:
 1070:  65: 
 1071:  66: ```
 1072:  67: rename({symbol_name: "validateUser", new_name: "authenticateUser", dry_run: true})
 1073:  68: → 12 edits across 8 files
 1074:  69: → 10 graph edits (high confidence), 2 ast_search edits (review)
 1075:  70: → Changes: [{file_path, edits: [{line, old_text, new_text, confidence}]}]
 1076:  71: ```
 1077:  72: 
 1078:  73: **impact** — map all dependents first:
 1079:  74: 
 1080:  75: ```
 1081:  76: impact({target: "validateUser", direction: "upstream"})
 1082:  77: → d=1: loginHandler, apiMiddleware, testUtils
 1083:  78: → Affected Processes: LoginFlow, TokenRefresh
 1084:  79: ```
 1085:  80: 
 1086:  81: **detect_changes** — verify your changes after refactoring:
 1087:  82: 
 1088:  83: ```
 1089:  84: detect_changes({scope: "all"})
 1090:  85: → Changed: 8 files, 12 symbols
 1091:  86: → Affected processes: LoginFlow, TokenRefresh
 1092:  87: → Risk: MEDIUM
 1093:  88: ```
 1094:  89: 
 1095:  90: **cypher** — custom reference queries:
 1096:  91: 
 1097:  92: ```cypher
 1098:  93: MATCH (caller)-[:CodeRelation {type: 'CALLS'}]->(f:Function {name: "validateUser"})
 1099:  94: RETURN caller.name, caller.filePath ORDER BY caller.filePath
 1100:  95: ```
 1101:  96: 
 1102:  97: ## Risk Rules
 1103:  98: 
 1104:  99: | Risk Factor         | Mitigation                                |
 1105: 100: | ------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
 1106: 101: | Many callers (>5)   | Use rename for automated updates |
 1107: 102: | Cross-area refs     | Use detect_changes after to verify scope  |
 1108: 103: | String/dynamic refs | query to find them               |
 1109: 104: | External/public API | Version and deprecate properly            |
 1110: 105: 
 1111: 106: ## Example: Rename `validateUser` to `authenticateUser`
 1112: 107: 
 1113: 108: ```
 1114: 109: 1. rename({symbol_name: "validateUser", new_name: "authenticateUser", dry_run: true})
 1115: 110:    → 12 edits: 10 graph (safe), 2 ast_search (review)
 1116: 111:    → Files: validator.ts, login.ts, middleware.ts, config.json...
 1117: 112: 
 1118: 113: 2. Review ast_search edits (config.json: dynamic reference!)
 1119: 114: 
 1120: 115: 3. rename({symbol_name: "validateUser", new_name: "authenticateUser", dry_run: false})
 1121: 116:    → Applied 12 edits across 8 files
 1122: 117: 
 1123: 118: 4. detect_changes({scope: "all"})
 1124: 119:    → Affected: LoginFlow, TokenRefresh
 1125: 120:    → Risk: MEDIUM — run tests for these flows
 1126: 121: ```
 1127: </file>
