39815:  1: # Optimization Routing — Always On
39816:  2: 
39817:  3: ## Regla global
39818:  4: 
39819:  5: Token Saver y Caveman están siempre activos.
39820:  6: 
39821:  7: Memory MCP y Learning son transversales (always-on), pero la eleccion de engine es propiedad del routing segun intencion/contexto.
39822:  8: 
39823:  9: ## Perfil por tipo de tarea
39824: 10: 
39825: 11: | Tarea | Token Saver | Caveman |
39826: 12: | --- | --- | --- |
39827: 13: | Debug / bug / CLI | strict | full |
39828: 14: | Refactor | strict | full/lite |
39829: 15: | Legacy impact | balanced | lite |
39830: 16: | Arquitectura | balanced | lite |
39831: 17: | DBA / SQL | strict | full/lite |
39832: 18: | RAG local | balanced | lite |
39833: 19: | Azure RAG corporativo | evidence-first | evidence-first |
39834: 20: | Formación | balanced | didactic-lite |
39835: 21: | Community content | balanced | lite |
39836: 22: | Snapshot | strict | lite |
39837: 23: 
39838: 24: ## Prioridad
39839: 25: 
39840: 26: ```txt
39841: 27: Si requiere fuentes -> evidence-first.
39842: 28: Si requiere código -> strict.
39843: 29: Si requiere enseñanza -> didactic-lite.
39844: 30: ```
39845: </file>
